"hlId":"6de49c",
"children":[
"Male Hypogonadism"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_en_s22_1",
"title":{
"__html":"Diagnosis"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"523223",
"children":[
"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"ea2acb",
"children":[
"Male hypogonadism is present when sperm or testosterone production is decreased. It can be a primary (testicular) or secondary (typically hypothalamic-pituitary) condition."
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"1",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_en_s22_inline_t1"
],
"forceOpen":true
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_en_s22_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Causes and Testing"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"e4df53",
"children":[
"Causes and Testing"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"f1fcbb",
"children":[
"Testosterone deficiency is diagnosed with two 8:00 ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"small",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"AM"
]
},
" total testosterone levels below the reference range."
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"4911b5",
"children":[
"If the testosterone measurement is equivocal, measure free testosterone."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"eb15ce",
"children":[
"If the testosterone level is low, measure ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"luteinizing hormone",
"children":[
"LH"
]
},
","
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"follicle-stimulating hormone",
"children":[
"FSH"
]
},
","
]
},
" and prolactin levels."
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"2b5ea6",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Elevated LH and FSH"
]
},
" values indicate primary testicular failure. Some common causes include:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"77e781",
"children":[
"Klinefelter syndrome (check karyotype)"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"251bac",
"children":[
"atrophy secondary to mumps orchitis"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"e414ca",
"children":[
"autoimmune destruction"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"e8d6c7",
"children":[
"previous chemotherapy or pelvic irradiation"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"a29bb3",
"children":[
"hemochromatosis"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"a025c8",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Low or normal LH and FSH"
]
},
" levels indicate secondary hypogonadism. Important causes include:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"938097",
"children":[
"sleep apnea"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"a6d3b8",
"children":[
"hyperprolactinemia"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"5f0f58",
"children":[
"hypothalamic or pituitary disorders (hemochromatosis, pituitary/hypothalamic tumor)"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"8a56c3",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"alert",
"children":[
"use of opioids, anabolic steroids, or glucocorticoids"
]
},
" "
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"534651",
"children":[
"If secondary hypogonadism is confirmed, in addition to measuring prolactin, check iron studies to rule out hemochromatosis and obtain an MRI to evaluate for hypothalamic or pituitary lesions."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"51e4f7",
"children":[
"Men who self-administer anabolic steroids can come to medical attention because of infertility. Physical examination typically reveals acne, muscular hypertrophy, testicular atrophy, and gynecomastia (if the patient is using testosterone). Laboratory data show suppressed LH and FSH levels, variable testosterone levels, and otherwise normal pituitary function."
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"a2b030",
"children":[
"Do not measure serum testosterone if a patient is having regular morning erections, has no gynecomastia on examination, and has a normal genital examination."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_en_s22_3",
"title":{
"__html":"Treatment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"47b2da",
"children":[
"Testosterone can be administered by multiple routes. Before initiation of testosterone replacement and during therapy, routinely monitor hematocrit and ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"prostate-specific antigen",
"children":[
"PSA"
]
},
" to screen for the development of erythrocytosis and prostate cancer, respectively."
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"b47b7a",
"children":[
"Don't provide testosterone replacement therapy for nonspecific symptoms such as fatigue and weakness in the absence of unequivocal testosterone deficiency."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"e13847",
"children":[
"Testosterone therapy does not treat infertility (impairs spermatogenesis)."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
}
]
},
